obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (12243)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12243&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Scheduled Castes and`
  line `the Scheduled Tribes (Prevention of Atrocities) Act, 1989.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu & Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10-2019).`
  line
  line `2. 30th January, 1990, vide notification No. S.O. 106(E), dated 29th January, 1990, See Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (12244)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12244&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "atrocity" means an offence punishable under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Code" means the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(bb)"dependent" means the spouse, children, parents, brother and sister of the victim, who are`
  line `dependent wholly or mainly on such victim for his support and maintenance;`
  line
  line `(bc) "economic boycott" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a refusal to deal with, work for hire or do business with other person; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to deny opportunities including access to services or contractual opportunities for`
  line `rendering service for consideration; or`
  line
  line `(iii) to refuse to do anything on the terms on which things would be commonly done in the`
  line `ordinary course of business; or`
  line
  line `(iv) to abstain from the professional or business relations that onewould maintain with other`
  line person;
  line
  line `(bd) "Exclusive Special Court" means the Exclusive Special Court established under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 14 exclusively to try the offences under this Act;`
  line
  line `(be) "forest rights" shall have the meaning assigned to it in sub-section (1) of section 3 of the`
  line `Scheduled Tribes and Other Traditional Forest Dwellers(Recognition of Forest Rights) Act, 2006`
  line `(2 of 2007);`
  line
  line `(bf) "manual scavenger" shall have the meaning assigned to it in clause (g) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Prohibition of Employment as Manual Scavengers and their Rehabilitation Act, 2013`
  line `(25 of 2013);`
  line
  line `(bg) "public servant" means a public servant as defined under section 21of the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860), as well as any other person deemed to be a public servant under any other law for the time being in force and includes any personacting in his official capacity under the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(c) "Scheduled Castes and Scheduled Tribes" shall have the meanings assigned to them`
  line `respectively under clause (24) and clause (25) of article 366 of the Constitution;`
  line
  line `(d) "Special Court" means a Court of Session specified as a Special Court in section 14;`
  line
  line `(e) "Special Public Prosecutor" means a Public Prosecutor specified as a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor or an advocate referred to in section 15;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ea) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(eb) "social boycott" means a refusal to permit a person to render to other person or receive from`
  line `him any customary service or to abstain from social relations that one would maintain with other`
  line `person or to isolate him from others;`
  line
  line `(ec) "victim" means any individual who falls within the definition of the "Scheduled Castes and`
  line `Scheduled Tribes" under clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 2, and who has suffered or`
  line `experienced physical, mental, psychological, emotional or monetary harm or harm to his property as a`
  line `result of the commission of any offence under this Act and includes his relatives, legal guardian and`
  line `legal heirs;`
  line
  line `(ed) "witness" means any person who is acquainted with the facts and circumstances, or is in`
  line `possession of any information or has knowledge necessary for the purpose of investigation, inquiry or`
  line `trial of any crime involving an offence under this Act, and who is or may be required to give`
  line `information or make a statement or produce any document during investigation, inquiry or trial of`
  line `such case and includes a victim of such offence;]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(f) the words and expressions used but not defined in this Act and defined in the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860), the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872) or the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974), as the case may be, shall be deemed to have the meanings respectively assigned to`
  line `them in those enactments.]`
  line
  line `(2) Any reference in this Act to any enactment or any provision thereof shall, in relation to an area in`
  line `which such enactment or such provision is not in force, be construed as a reference to the corresponding`
  line `law, if any, in force in that area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 3 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3,ibid., for clause (f) (w.e.f. 26-1-2016)`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (12245)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Punishments for offences atrocities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12245&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Whoever, not being a member of a Scheduled Caste`
  line `or a Scheduled Tribe,--`
  line
  line `(a) puts any inedible or obnoxious substance into the mouth of a member of a Scheduled Caste or`
  line `a Scheduled Tribe or forces such member to drink or eat such inedible or obnoxious substance;`
  line
  line `(b) dumps excreta, sewage, carcasses or any other obnoxious substance in premises, or at the`
  line `entrance of the premises, occupied by a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(c) with intent to cause injury, insult or annoyance to any member of a Scheduled Caste or a`
  line `Scheduled Tribe, dumps excreta, waste matter, carcasses or any other obnoxious substance in his`
  line neighbourhood;
  line
  line `(d) garlands with footwear or parades naked or semi-naked a member of a Scheduled Caste or a`
  line `Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(e) forcibly commits on a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe any act, such as`
  line `removing clothes from the person, forcible tonsuring of head, removing moustaches, painting face or`
  line `body or any other similar act, which is derogatory to human dignity;`
  line
  line `(f) wrongfully occupies or cultivates any land, owned by, or in the possession of or allotted to, or`
  line `notified by any competent authority to be allotted to, a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled`
  line `Tribe, or gets such land transferred;`
  line
  line `(g) wrongfully dispossesses a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe from his land or`
  line `premises or interferes with the enjoyment of his rights, including forest rights, over any land or`
  line `premises or water or irrigation facilities or destroys the crops or takes away the produce therefrom.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of clause (f) and this clause, the expression "wrongfully"`
  line includes--
  line
  line `(A) against the person's will;`
  line
  line `(B) without the person's consent;`
  line
  line `(C) with the person's consent, where such consent has been obtained by putting the person, or`
  line `any other person in whom the person is interested in fear of death or of hurt; or`
  line
  line `(D) fabricating records of such land;`
  line
  line `(h) makes a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to do "begar" or other forms of`
  line `forced or bonded labour other than any compulsory service for public purposes imposed by the`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(i) compels a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to dispose or carry human or`
  line `animal carcasses, or to dig graves;`
  line
  line `(j) makes a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to do manual scavenging or`
  line `employs or permits the employment of such member for such purpose;`
  line
  line `(k) performs, or promotes dedicating a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe woman to a deity,`
  line `idol, object of worship, temple, or other religious institution as a deva dasi or any other similar`
  line `practice or permits aforementioned acts;`
  line
  line `(l) forces or intimidates or prevents a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe--`
  line
  line `(A) not to vote or to vote for a particular candidate or to vote in a manner other than that`
  line `provided by law;`
  line
  line `(B) not to file a nomination as a candidate or to withdraw such nomination; or`
  line
  line `(C) not to propose or second the nomination of a member of a Scheduled Caste or a`
  line `Scheduled Tribe as a candidate in any election;`
  line
  line `(m) forces or intimidates or obstructs a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe, who`
  line `is a member or a Chairperson or a holder of any other office of a Panchayat under Part IX of the`
  line `Constitution or a Municipality under Part IXA of the Constitution, from performing their normal`
  line `duties and functions;`
  line
  line `(n) after the poll, causes hurt or grievous hurt or assault or imposes or threatens to impose social`
  line `or economic boycott upon a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe or prevents from`
  line `availing benefits of any public service which is due to him;`
  line
  line `(o) commits any offence under this Act against a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled`
  line `Tribe for having voted or not having voted for a particular candidate or for having voted in a manner`
  line `provided by law;`
  line
  line `(p) institutes false, malicious or vexatious suit or criminal or other legal proceedings against a`
  line `member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(q) gives any false or frivolous information to any public servant and thereby causes such public`
  line `servant to use his lawful power to the injury or annoyance of a member of a Scheduled Caste or a`
  line `Scheduled Tribe;`
  line
  line `(r) intentionally insults or intimidates with intent to humiliate a member of a Scheduled Caste or a`
  line `Scheduled Tribe in any place within public view;`
  line
  line `(s) abuses any member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe by caste name in any place`
  line `within public view;`
  line
  line `(t) destroys, damages or defiles any object generally known to be held sacred or in high esteem by`
  line `members of the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this clause, the expression "object" means and includes statue,`
  line `photograph and portrait;`
  line
  line `(u) by words either written or spoken or by signs or by visible representation or otherwise`
  line `promotes or attempts to promote feelings of enmity, hatred or ill-will against members of the`
  line `Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(v) by words either written or spoken or by any other means disrespects any late person held in`
  line `high esteem by members of the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(w) (i) intentionally touches a woman belonging to a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe,`
  line `knowing that she belongs to a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe, when such act of touching is of`
  line `a sexual nature and is without the recipients consent;`
  line
  line `(ii) uses words, acts or gestures of a sexual nature towards a woman belonging to a Scheduled`
  line `Caste or a Scheduled Tribe, knowing that she belongs to a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-clause (i), the expression "consent" means an unequivocal`
  line `voluntary agreement when the person by words, gestures, or any form of non-verbal communication,`
  line `communicates willingness to participate in the specific act:`
  line
  line `Provided that a woman belonging to a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe who does not offer`
  line `physical resistance to any act of a sexual nature is not by reason only of that fact, is to be regarded as`
  line `consenting to the sexual activity:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a woman's sexual history, including with the offender shall not imply`
  line `consent or mitigate the offence;`
  line
  line `(x) corrupts or fouls the water of any spring, reservoir or any other source ordinarily used by`
  line `members of the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes so as to render it less fit for the purpose for`
  line `which it is ordinarily used;`
  line
  line `(y) denies a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe any customary right of passage to`
  line `a place of public resort or obstructs such member so as to prevent him from using or having access to`
  line `a place of public resort to which other members of public or any other section thereof have a right to`
  line `use or access to;`
  line
  line `(z) forces or causes a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to leave his house,`
  line `village or other place of residence:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this clause shall apply to any action taken in discharge of a`
  line `public duty;`
  line
  line `(za) obstructs or prevents a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe in any manner`
  line `with regard to--`
  line
  line `(A) using common property resources of an area, or burial or cremation ground equally with`
  line `others or using any river, stream, spring, well, tank, cistern, water-tap or other watering place, or`
  line `any bathing ghat, any public conveyance, any road, or passage;`
  line
  line `(B) mounting or riding bicycles or motor cycles or wearing footwear or new clothes in public`
  line `places or taking out wedding procession, or mounting a horse or any other vehicle during`
  line `wedding processions;`
  line
  line `(C) entering any place of worship which is open to the public or other persons professing the`
  line `same religion or taking part in, or taking out, any religious, social or cultural processions`
  line `including jatras;`
  line
  line `(D) entering any educational institution, hospital, dispensary, primary health centre, shop or`
  line `place of public entertainment or any other public place; or using any utensils or articles meant for`
  line `public use in any place open to the public; or`
  line
  line `(E) practicing any profession or the carrying on of any occupation, trade or business or`
  line `employment in any job which other members of the public, or any section thereof, have a right to`
  line `use or have access to;`
  line
  line `(zb) causes physical harm or mental agony of a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled`
  line `Tribe on the allegation of practicing witchcraft or being a witch; or`
  line
  line `(zc) imposes or threatens a social or economic boycott of any person or a family or a group`
  line `belonging to a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to five years and with fine.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, not being a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe,--`
  line
  line `(i) gives or fabricates false evidence intending thereby to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he`
  line `will thereby cause, any member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to be convicted of an`
  line `offence which is capital by the law for the time being in force shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `for life and with fine; and if an innocent member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe be`
  line `convicted and executed in consequence of such false or fabricated evidence, the person who gives or`
  line `fabricates such false evidence, shall be punished with death;`
  line
  line `(ii) gives or fabricates false evidence intending thereby to cause, or knowing it to be likely that he`
  line `will thereby cause, any member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe to be convicted of an`
  line `offence which is not capital but punishable with imprisonment for a term of seven years or upwards,`
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which`
  line `may extend to seven years or upwards and with fine;`
  line
  line `(iii) commits mischief by fire or any explosive substance intending to cause or knowing it to be`
  line `likely that he will thereby cause damage to any property belonging to a member of a Scheduled Caste`
  line `or a Scheduled Tribe, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than`
  line `six months but which may extend to seven years and with fine;`
  line
  line `(iv) commits mischief by fire or any explosive substance intending to cause or knowing it to be`
  line `likely that he will thereby cause destruction of any building which is ordinarily used as a place of`
  line `worship or as a place for human dwelling or as a place for custody of the property by a member of a`
  line `Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe, shall be punishable with imprisonment for life and with fine;`
  line
  line `(v) commits any offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term of ten years or more against a person or property ^2[knowing that such person is a member`
  line `of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe or such property belongs to such member], shall be`
  line `punishable with imprisonment for life and with fine;`
  line
  line `^3[(va) commits any offence specified in the Schedule, against a person or property, knowing that`
  line `such person is a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe or such property belongs to suchmember, shall be punishable with such punishment as specified under the Indian Penal Code`
  line `(45 of 1860) for such offences and shall also be liable to fine;]`
  line
  line `(vi) knowingly or having reason to believe that an offence has been committed under this`
  line `Chapter, causes any evidence of the commission of that offence to disappear with the intention of`
  line `screening the offender from legal punishment, or with that intention gives any information respecting`
  line `the offence which he knows or believes to be false, shall be punishable with the punishment provided`
  line `for that offence; or`
  line
  line `(vii) being a public servant, commits any offence under this section, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but which may extend to the`
  line `punishment provided for that offence`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 4, for "on the ground that such person is a member of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe or`
  line `such property belongs to such member" (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (12246)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Punishment for neglect of duties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 5, for section 4 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12246&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[4. Punishment for neglect of duties.--(1) Whoever, being a public servant but not being a member`
  line `of a Scheduled Caste or a Scheduled Tribe, wilfully neglects his duties required to be performed by him`
  line `under this Act and the rules made thereunder, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which`
  line `shall not be less than six months but which may extend to one year.`
  line
  line `(2) The duties of public servant referred to in sub-section (1) shall include--`
  line
  line `(a) to read out to an informant the information given orally, and reduced to writing by the officer`
  line `in charge of the police station, before taking the signature of the informant;`
  line
  line `(b) to register a complaint or a First Information Report under this Act and other relevant`
  line `provisions and to register it under appropriate sections of this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) to furnish a copy of the information so recorded forthwith to the in formant;`
  line
  line `(d) to record the statement of the victims or witnesses;`
  line
  line `(e) to conduct the investigation and file charge sheet in the Special Court or the Exclusive Special`
  line `Court within a period of sixty days, and to explain the delay if any, in writing;`
  line
  line `(f) to correctly prepare, frame and translate any document or electronic record;`
  line
  line `(g) to perform any other duty specified in this Act or the rules made thereunder:`
  line
  line `Provided that the charges in this regard against the public servant shall be booked on the`
  line `recommendation of an administrative enquiry.`
  line
  line `(3) The cognizance in respect of any dereliction of duty referred to in sub-section (2) by a public`
  line `servant shall be taken by the Special Court or the Exclusive Special Court and shall give direction for`
  line `penal proceedings against such public servant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (12247)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Enhanced punishment subsequent conviction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12247&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, having already been convicted of an`
  line `offence under this Chapter is convicted for the second offence or any offence subsequent to the second`
  line `offence, shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one year but`
  line `which may extend to the punishment provided for that offence.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (12248)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Application of certain provisions of the Indian Penal Code.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12248&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the other provisions of`
  line `this Act, the provisions of section 34, Chapter III, Chapter IV, Chapter V, Chapter VA, section 149 and`
  line `Chapter XXIII of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), shall, so far as may be, apply for the purposes of`
  line `this Act as they apply for the purposes of the Indian Penal Code`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (12249)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Forfeiture of property of certain persons.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12249&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a person has been convicted of any`
  line `offence punishable under this Chapter, the Special Court may, in addition to awarding any punishment,`
  line `by order in writing, declare that any property, movable or immovable or both, belonging to the person,`
  line `which has been used for the commission of that offence, shall stand forfeited to Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person is accused of any offence under this Chapter, it shall be open to the Special`
  line `Court trying him to pass an order that all or any of the properties, movable or immovable or both, belonging to him, shall, during the period of such trial, be attached, and where such trial ends in`
  line `conviction, the property so attached shall be liable to forfeiture to the extent it is required for the purpose`
  line `of realisation of any fine imposed under this Chapter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (12250)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Presumption as to offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12250&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `In a prosecution for an offence under this Chapter, if it is proved`
  line that--
  line
  line `(a) the accused rendered ^1`
  line `[any financial assistance in relation to the offences committed by a`
  line `person accused of], or reasonably suspected of, committing, an offence under this Chapter, the`
  line `Special Court shall presume, unless the contrary is proved, that such person had abetted the offence;`
  line
  line `(b) a group of persons committed an offence under this Chapter and if it is proved that the offence`
  line `committed was a sequel to any existing dispute regarding land or any other matter, it shall be`
  line `presumed that the offence was committed in furtherance of the common intention or in prosecution of`
  line `the common object;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(c) the accused was having personal knowledge of the victim or his family, the Court shall`
  line `presume that the accused was aware of the caste or tribal identity of the victim, unless the contrary is`
  line proved.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 6, for "any financial assistance to a person accused of" (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 6, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (12251)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Conferment of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12251&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code or in any other`
  line `provision of this Act, the State Government may, if it considers it necessary or expedient so to do,--`
  line
  line `(a) for the prevention of and for coping with any offence under this Act, or`
  line
  line `(b) for any case or class or group of cases under this Act,`
  line
  line `in any district or part thereof, confer, by notification in the Official Gazette, on any officer of the State`
  line `Government, the powers exercisable by a police officer under the Code in such district or part thereof or,`
  line `as the case may be, for such case or class or group of cases, and in particular, the powers of arrest,`
  line `investigation and prosecution of persons before any Special Court.`
  line
  line `(2) All officers of police and all other officers of Government shall assist the officer referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) in the execution of the provisions of this Act or any rule, scheme or order made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(3) The provisions of the Code shall, so far as may be, apply to the exercise of the powers by an`
  line `officer under sub-section (1).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (12252)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal of person likely to commit offence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12252&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Special Court is satisfied, upon a`
  line `complaint or a police report that a person is likely to commit an offence under Chapter II of this Act in`
  line `any area included in "Scheduled Areas" or "tribal areas", as referred to in article 244 of the Constitution,`
  line ^1
  line `[or any area identified under the provisions of clause (vii) of sub-section (2) of section 21], it may, by`
  line `order in writing, direct such person to remove himself beyond the limits of such area, by such route and`
  line `within such time as may be specified in the order, and not to return to that area from which he was`
  line `directed to remove himself for such period, not exceeding ^2`
  line `[three years], as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Court shall, along with the order under sub-section (1), communicate to the person`
  line `directed under that sub-section the grounds on which such order has been made.`
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court may revoke or modify the order made under sub-section (1), for the reasons to`
  line `be recorded in writing, on the representation made by the person against whom such order has been made`
  line `or by any other person on his behalf within thirty days from the date of the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for "two years" (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (12253)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Procedure on failure of person to remove himself from area and enter thereon after removal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12253&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person to whom a direction has been issued under section 10 to remove himself from`
  line `any area--`
  line
  line `(a) fails to remove himself as directed; or`
  line
  line `(b) having so removed himself enters such area within the period specified in the order,`
  line
  line `otherwise than with the permission in writing of the Special Court under sub-section (2), the Special`
  line `Court may cause him to be arrested and removed in police custody to such place outside such area as the`
  line `Special Court may specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Court may, by order in writing, permit any person in respect of whom an order under`
  line `section 10 has been made, to return to the area from which he was directed to remove himself for such`
  line `temporary period and subject to such conditions as may be specified in such order and may require him to`
  line `execute a bond with or without surety for the due observation of the conditions imposed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Special Court may at any time revoke any such permission.`
  line
  line `(4) Any person who, with such permission, returns to the area from which he was directed to remove`
  line `himself shall observe the conditions imposed, and at the expiry of the temporary period for which he was`
  line `permitted to return, or on the revocation of such permission before the expiry of such temporary period,`
  line `shall remove himself outside such area and shall not return thereto within the unexpired portion specified`
  line `under section 10 without a fresh permission.`
  line
  line `(5) If a person fails to observe any of the conditions imposed or to remove himself accordingly or`
  line `having so removed himself enters or returns to such area without fresh permission the Special Court may`
  line `cause him to be arrested and removed in police custody to such place outside such area as the Special`
  line `Court may specify`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (12254)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Taking measurements and photographs, etc., of persons against whom order under section 10 is made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12254&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person against whom an order has been made under section 10 shall, if so`
  line `required by the Special Court, allow his measurements and photographs to be taken by a police officer.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person referred to in sub-section (1), when required to allow his measurements or`
  line `photographs to be taken, resists or refuses to allow the taking of such measurements or photographs, it`
  line `shall be lawful to use all necessary means to secure the taking thereof.`
  line
  line `(3) Resistance to or refusal to allow the taking of measurements or photographs under sub-section (2)`
  line `shall be deemed to be an offence under section 186 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(4) Where an order under section 10 is revoked, all measurements and photographs (including`
  line `negatives) taken under sub-section (2) shall be destroyed or made over to the person against whom such`
  line `order is made.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (12255)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Penalty for noncompliance of order under section 10.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12255&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Any person contravening an order of`
  line `the Special Court made under section 10 shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year and with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (12256)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Special Court and Exclusive Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 1 of 2016, s. 8,for section 14 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12256&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[14. Special Court and Exclusive Special Court.--(1) For the purpose of providing for speedy`
  line `trial, the State Government shall, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, establish an Exclusive Special Court for one or more Districts:`
  line
  line `Provided that in Districts where less number of cases under this Act is recorded, the State`
  line `Government shall, with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify for such Districts, the Court of Session to be a Special Court to try the offences`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Courts so established or specified shall have power to directly take`
  line `cognizance of offences under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall be the duty of the State Government to establish adequate number of Courts to ensure that`
  line `cases under this Act are disposed of within a period of two months, as far as possible.`
  line
  line `(3) In every trial in the Special Court or the Exclusive Special Court, the proceedings shall be`
  line `continued from day-to-day until all the witnesses in attendance have been examined, unless the Special`
  line `Court or the Exclusive Special Court finds the adjournment of the same beyond the following day to be`
  line `necessary for reasons to be recorded in writing:]`
  line
  line `Provided that when the trial relates to an offence under this Act, the trial shall, as far as possible, be`
  line `completed within a period of two months from the date of filing of the charge sheet.`
  line
  line `STATE AMENDMENT`
  line
  line Karnataka
  line
  line `Amendment of section 14.--In section 14 of the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes`
  line `(Prevention of Atrocities) Act, 1989 (Central Act 33 of 1989), for the words “to try offences under this`
  line `Act”, the words “to take cognizance of offences under this Act as a court of original jurisdiction and to try`
  line `such offences” shall be substituted.`
  line
  line `[Vide Karnataka Act 35 of 2003, s. 2 ]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_a:
  sectionId (12257)
  sectionNo 14A
  orderNo 15
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act1 of 2016, s. 9 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12257&sectionno=14A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_14_a_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[14A. Appeals.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure,1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), an appeal shall lie, from any judgment, sentence or order, not being an interlocutory order, of`
  line `a Special Court or an Exclusive Special Court, to the High Court both on facts and on law.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (3) of section 378 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), an appeal shall lie to the High Court against an order of the Special Court or`
  line `the Exclusive Special Court granting or refusing bail.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, every appeal`
  line `under this section shall be preferred within a period of ninety days from the date of the judgment,`
  line `sentence or order appealed from:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said period of ninety days`
  line `if it is satisfied that the appellant had sufficient cause for not preferring the appeal within the period of`
  line `ninety days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no appeal shall be entertained after the expiry of the period of one hundred and`
  line `eighty days.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal preferred under sub-section (1) shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within a`
  line `period of three months from the date of admission of the appeal.]br`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (12258)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Special Public Prosecutor and Exclusive Public Prosecutor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s.10, ibid., for section 15 (w.e.f. 26-1-2016)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12258&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[15. Special Public Prosecutor and Exclusive Public Prosecutor.--(1) For every Special Court,`
  line `the State Government shall, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify a Public Prosecutor or appoint`
  line `an advocate who has been in practice as an advocate for not less than seven years, as a Special Public`
  line `Prosecutor for the purpose of conducting cases in that Court.`
  line
  line `(2) For every Exclusive Special Court, the State Government shall, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify an Exclusive Special Public Prosecutor or appoint an advocate who has been in practice`
  line `as an advocate for not less than seven years, as an Exclusive Special Public Prosecutor for the purpose of`
  line `conducting cases in that Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (12259)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 17
  title `Rights of victims and witnesses.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 26-1-2016).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12259&sectionno=15A&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^115A. Rights of victims and witnesses.--(1) It shall be the duty and responsibility of the State to`
  line `make arrangements for the protection of victims, their dependents, and witnesses against any kind of`
  line `intimidation or coercion or inducement or violence or threats of violence.`
  line
  line `(2) A victim shall be treated with fairness, respect and dignity and with due regard to any special need`
  line `that arises because of the victims age or gender or educational disadvantage or poverty.`
  line
  line `(3) A victim or his dependent shall have the right to reasonable, accurate, and timely notice of any`
  line `Court proceeding including any bail proceeding and the Special Public Prosecutor or the State`
  line `Government shall inform the victim about any proceedings under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) A victim or his dependent shall have the right to apply to the Special Court or the Exclusive`
  line `Special Court, as the case may be, to summon parties for production of any documents or material,`
  line `witnesses or examine the persons present.`
  line
  line `(5) A victim or his dependent shall be entitled to be heard at any proceeding under this Act in respect`
  line `of bail, discharge, release, parole, conviction or sentence of an accused or any connected proceedings or`
  line `arguments and file written submission on conviction, acquittal or sentencing.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure,1973 (2 of 1974), the`
  line `Special Court or the Exclusive Special Court trying a case under this Act shall provide to a victim, his`
  line `dependent, informant or witnesses--`
  line
  line `(a) the complete protection to secure the ends of justice;`
  line
  line `(b) the travelling and maintenance expenses during investigation, inquiry and trial;`
  line
  line `(c) the social-economic rehabilitation during investigation, inquiry and trial; and`
  line
  line `(d) relocation.`
  line
  line `(7) The State shall inform the concerned Special Court or the Exclusive Special Court about the`
  line `protection provided to any victim or his dependent, informant or witnesses and such Court shall`
  line `periodically review the protection being offered and pass appropriate orders.`
  line
  line `(8) Without prejudice to the generality of the provisions of sub-section (6), the concerned Special`
  line `Court or the Exclusive Special Court may, on an application made by a victim or his dependent,`
  line `informant or witness in any proceedings before it or by the Special Public Prosecutor in relation to such`
  line `victim, informant or witness or on its own motion, take such measures including--`
  line
  line `(a) concealing the names and addresses of the witnesses in its orders or judgments or in any`
  line `records of the case accessible to the public;`
  line
  line `(b) issuing directions for non-disclosure of the identity and addresses of the witnesses;`
  line
  line `(c) take immediate action in respect of any complaint relating to harassment of a victim,`
  line `informant or witness and on the same day, if necessary, pass appropriate orders for protection:`
  line
  line `Provided that inquiry or investigation into the complaint received under clause (c) shall be tried`
  line `separately from the main case by such Court and concluded within a period of two months from the`
  line `date of receipt of the complaint:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the complaint under clause (c) is against any public servant, the Court`
  line `shall restrain such public servant from interfering with the victim, informant or witness, as the case`
  line `may be, in any matter related or unrelated to the pending case, except with the permission of the`
  line Court.
  line
  line `(9) It shall be the duty of the Investigating Officer and the Station House Officer to record the`
  line `complaint of victim, informant or witnesses against any kind of intimidation, coercion or inducement or`
  line `violence or threats of violence, whether given orally or in writing, and a photocopy of the First`
  line `Information Report shall be immediately given to them at free of cost.`
  line
  line `(10) All proceedings relating to offences under this Act shall be video recorded.`
  line
  line `(11) It shall be the duty of the concerned State to specify an appropriate scheme to ensure`
  line `implementation of the following rights and entitlements of victims and witnesses in accessing justice so`
  line as--
  line
  line `(a) to provide a copy of the recorded First Information Report at free of cost;`
  line
  line `(b) to provide immediate relief in cash or in kind to atrocity victims or their dependents;`
  line
  line `(c) to provide necessary protection to the atrocity victims or their dependents, and witnesses;`
  line
  line `(d) to provide relief in respect of death or injury or damage to property;`
  line
  line `(e) to arrange food or water or clothing or shelter or medical aid or transport facilities or daily`
  line `allowances to victims;`
  line
  line `(f) to provide the maintenance expenses to the atrocity victims and their dependents;`
  line
  line `(g) to provide the information about the rights of atrocity victims at the time of making`
  line `complaints and registering the First Information Report;`
  line
  line `(h) to provide the protection to atrocity victims or their dependents and witnesses from`
  line `intimidation and harassment;`
  line
  line `(i) to provide the information to atrocity victims or their dependents or associated organisations or`
  line `individuals, on the status of investigation and charge sheet and to provide copy of the charge sheet at`
  line `free of cost;`
  line
  line `(j) to take necessary precautions at the time of medical examination;`
  line
  line `(k) to provide information to atrocity victims or their dependents or associated organisations or`
  line `individuals, regarding the relief amount;`
  line
  line `(l) to provide information to atrocity victims or their dependents or associated organisations or`
  line `individuals, in advance about the dates and place of investigation and trial;`
  line
  line `(m) to give adequate briefing on the case and preparation for trial to atrocity victims or their`
  line `dependents or associated organisations or individuals and to provide the legal aid for the said purpose;`
  line
  line `(n) to execute the rights of atrocity victims or their dependents or associated organisations or`
  line `individuals at every stage of the proceedings under this Act and to provide the necessary assistance`
  line `for the execution of the rights.`
  line
  line `(12) It shall be the right of the atrocity victims or their dependents, to take assistance from the NonGovernment`
  line `Organisations, social workers or advocates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (12260)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of State Government to impose collective fine.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12260&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 10A of the`
  line `Protection of Civil Rights Act, 1955 (22 of 1955) shall, so far as may be, apply for the purposes of`
  line `imposition and realisation of collective fine and for all other matters connected therewith under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (12261)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Preventive action to be taken by the law and order machinery.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12261&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) A District Magistrate or a`
  line `Sub-divisional Magistrate or any other Executive Magistrate or any police officer not below the rank of a`
  line `Deputy Superintendent of Police may, on receiving information and after such inquiry as he may think`
  line `necessary, has reason to believe that a person or a group of persons not belonging to the Scheduled Castes`
  line `or the Scheduled Tribes, residing in or frequenting any place within the local limits of his jurisdiction is`
  line `likely to commit an offence or has threatened to commit any offence under this Act and is of the opinion`
  line `that there is sufficient ground for proceeding, declare such an area to be an area prone to atrocities and`
  line `take necessary action for keeping the peace and good behaviour and maintenance of public order and`
  line `tranquillity and may take preventive action.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of Chapters VIII, X and XI of the Code shall, so far as may be, apply for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make one or more schemes`
  line `specifying the manner in which the officers referred to in sub-section (1) shall take appropriate action`
  line `specified in such scheme or schemes to prevent atrocities and to restore the feeling of security amongst`
  line `the members of the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (12262)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Section 438 of the Code not to apply to persons committing an offence under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12262&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in section 438 of the Code shall apply in relation to any case involving the arrest of any person`
  line `on an accusation of having committed an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (49378)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 21
  title `No enquiry or approval required.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2018, s. 2 (w.e.f. 20-8-2018)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=49378&sectionno=18A&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. No enquiry or approval required.-- (1) For the purposes of this Act,--`
  line
  line `a) preliminary enquiry shall not be required for registration of a First Information Report against`
  line `any person; or`
  line
  line `(b) the investigating officer shall not require approval for the arrest, if necessary, of any person,`
  line `against whom an accusation of having committed an offence under this Act has been made and no`
  line `procedure other than that provided under this Act or the Code shall apply.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of section 438 of the Code shall not apply to a case under this Act,`
  line `notwithstanding any judgment or order or direction of any Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (12263)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 22
  title `Section 360 of the Code or the provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act not to apply to persons guilty of an offence under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12263&sectionno=19&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of section 360 of the Code and the`
  line `provisions of the Probation of Offenders Act, 1958 (20 of 1958) shall not apply to any person above the`
  line `age of eighteen years who is found guilty of having committed an offence under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (12264)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 23
  title `Act to override other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12264&sectionno=20&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided in this Act, the provisions of this Act`
  line `shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force or any custom or usage or any instrument having effect by virtue of any such law`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (12265)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 24
  title `Duty of Government to ensure effective implementation of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12265&sectionno=21&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such rules`
  line `as the Central Government may make in this behalf, the State Government shall take such measures as`
  line `may be necessary for the effective implementation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing provisions, such measures`
  line `may include,--`
  line
  line `(i) the provision for adequate facilities, including legal aid, to the persons subjected to atrocities`
  line `to enable them to avail themselves of justice;`
  line
  line `(ii) the provision for travelling and maintenance expenses to witnesses, including the victims of`
  line `atrocities, during investigation and trial of offences under this Act;`
  line
  line `(iii) the provision for the economic and social rehabilitation of the victims of the atrocities;`
  line
  line `(iv) the appointment of officers for initiating or exercising supervision over prosecutions for the`
  line `contravention of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `(v) the setting up of committees at such appropriate levels as the State Government may think fit`
  line `to assist that Government in formulation or implementation of such measures;`
  line
  line `(vi) provision for a periodic survey of the working of the provisions of this Act with a view to`
  line `suggesting measures for the better implementation of the provision of this Act;`
  line
  line `(vii) the identification of the areas where the members of the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled`
  line `Tribes are likely to be subjected to atrocities and adoption of such measures so as to ensure safety for`
  line `such members.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government shall take such steps as may be necessary to co-ordinate the measures`
  line `taken by the State Governments under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government shall, every year, place on the table of each House of Parliament a report`
  line `on the measures taken by itself and by the State Governments in pursuance of the provisions of this`
  line section.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (12266)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12266&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceedings shall`
  line `lie against the Central Government or against the State Government or any officer or authority of`
  line `Government or any other person for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (12267)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896&sectionId=12267&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_25_35_00002_198933_1517807322896
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House`
  line `of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
